{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
ni = 100
no = 2
xb, yb = torch.randn(32, ni).cuda(), torch.randint(no, (32,)).cuda()
def simple_model(ni=100, no=2, n=4):
    layers = [nn.Linear(ni, ni) for i in range(n)] + [nn.Linear(ni,no)]
    return nn.Sequential(*layers)
